President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of a Chairman and an Executive Secretary for the Petroleum Product Pricing Regulatory Agency (PPPRA). The Chairman, Mr Atuonwo A. Obinna, while the Executive Secretary Mr Abdulkadir Saidu was reappointed for another four years, according to a statement signed by Femi Adesina, the Presidentâ€™s Spokesman. The appointment of Mr Atuonwo Obinna as Chairman Governing Board for a four-year term is in accordance with Section 2 (1-3) and 3 (a) of the Petroleum Product Pricing Regulatory Agency (Establishment, ETC) Act 2003.